# Caching

- Cache only data that is expensive to compute/fetch and safe to be slightly stale.
- Always define TTL; unbounded caches cause memory leaks and stale data bugs.
- Use cache-aside pattern: app checks cache → on miss, fetch DB → populate cache.
- Invalidate on write, not just TTL, for user-facing mutable data.
- Use consistent cache keys: `{entity}:{id}:{version}` — include schema version when needed.
- Prefer Redis/Memcached for distributed cache; avoid local-only cache in multi-instance deploys.
- Do not cache error responses unless intentional (with short TTL).
- Monitor cache hit rate, eviction rate, and memory usage.
- Cache at the right layer: CDN for static assets, Redis for API responses, in-process for hot paths only.
- Document cache invalidation strategy in code comments for non-obvious cases.
